title: Montgomery soccer group to raise money for high school program
text: Montgomery soccer group to raise money for high school program Posted: MONTGOMERY, AL (WSFA) - From the Montgomery Chapter of the American Outlaws: The Montgomery chapter of the American Outlaws will hold their first ever Footgolf Tournament at Tallapoosa Lakes Golf Course on Saturday, October 10 at 3 PM. The event will benefit the Jeff Davis High School soccer program. The Footgolf tournament is open to the community at large, and spots are limited. If you are interested in participating or have questions, please write to The American Outlaws: Montgomery are a passionate group of U.S soccer fans dedicated to growing interest and appreciation of the game of soccer, and positively impacting the River Region. For more information on the event, see our Facebook page at https://www.facebook.com/events/457134504458749/ , and read more about theAmerican Outlaws at www.theamericanoutlaws.com .
